<h2>What Is Technical SEO?</h2>

<p>
Technical SEO is the process of optimizing your website so that search engines can:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Crawl your site</li>
<li>Index your pages</li>
<li>Understand your content</li>
</ul>

<p>
Without this, your website may never appear on Google.
</p>

<p>
Businesses invest in  
<a href="#services" style="color:#f39c12;font-weight:bold;">
technical SEO services in Kenya
</a>  
to fix these issues.
</p>

---

<h2>1. Website Crawling & Indexing</h2>

<p>
Search engines use bots to crawl your website.
</p>

<p>
If your site is not crawlable:
👉 It will not rank
</p>

<p>
Check:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Robots.txt</li>
<li>XML sitemap</li>
<li>Broken links</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>2. Website Speed Optimization</h2>

<p>
Speed is a ranking factor.
</p>

<p>
Slow sites:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Lose visitors</li>
<li>Rank lower</li>
</ul>

<p>
Improve speed by:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Compressing images</li>
<li>Reducing scripts</li>
<li>Using caching</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>3. Mobile-Friendliness</h2>

<p>
Most users browse on mobile.
</p>

<p>
Your site must:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Be responsive</li>
<li>Load fast on mobile</li>
<li>Be easy to navigate</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>4. Secure Website (HTTPS)</h2>

<p>
Security is important for SEO.
</p>

<p>
Google prefers:
👉 HTTPS websites
</p>

<p>
If your site is not secure, rankings may drop.
</p>

---

<h2>5. URL Structure Optimization</h2>

<p>
URLs should be:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Short</li>
<li>Keyword-rich</li>
<li>Clean</li>
</ul>

<p>
Example:
</p>

<p>
<strong>/blog/technical-seo-explained-2026.html</strong>
</p>

---

<h2>6. Fix Broken Links</h2>

<p>
Broken links hurt SEO.
</p>

<p>
They:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Reduce user experience</li>
<li>Stop search engines from crawling</li>
</ul>

<p>
Fix them regularly.
</p>

---

